abstract: LONG before her children were born, Sheila Berkley was designing playground equipment. "I wanted to make accessible things that could change people's perceptions of everyday spaces," said Miss Berkley, shown at left with her 2-year-old son, Hugh. (There's also Allison, 6, and  9-week-old Amy).

abstract: LAS VEGAS, Nev., March 23 (AP)-- Donna Caponi Young, despite a bogey on the 18th hole, carded a two-underpar 70 today to gain a one-shot victory over Nancy Lopez-Melton, the defender, in the $200,000 Ladies' Professional Golf Association National Pro-Am tournament.

abstract: Saying tnat Jimmy Carter was "busy with international crises" and that Amy had a violin lesson, Rosalynn Carter stumped through Brooklyn and Yonkers yesterday, asking voters to unite behind the President in the state primary on Tuesday and promising that the poor would not be hurt by proposed budget cuts.

abstract: DARIEN  "COMPANY," the 1970 Stephen Sondheim hit, is a far cry from standard dinner-thea  ter fare. It has little of the sweetness and schmaltz that usually turns up after the roast beef buffet, and I congratulate the Darien Dinner Theater for doing it.

PONTE VEDRA, Fla., March 22-- Lee Trevino says he tries to win every time he tees it up. "It doesn't always happen, but that's in my mind," he adds. Tomorrow Trevino stands a good chance of winning his first golf tournament this season because after three rounds he leads the Tournament Players Championship, the showcase event of the PGA Tour.
